This paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) and specifically focuses on developing language technologies for code-switching data. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves crowd-sourcing and machine learning techniques, which could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper discusses the importance of high-quality linguistic annotations, which could be relevant to cs.SD (Software Engineering) and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
